OL,6,FAngie Langshaw, who was Mr Lupton's
OL,7,Fneighbour for more than two decades
OL,8,Fand a close friend, said: ''I feel
OL,9,Fbitter.
OL,11,F"If (a criminal conviction) happened
OL,12,Fto you or I it would just take a
OL,13,F(criminal records) check and you'd get
OL,14,Fwiped out.
OL,16,F"I find it bizarre someone can go back
OL,17,Fand practise as a family lawyer. We
OL,18,Fshould be the ones feeling we have
OL,19,Fjustice, but we haven't.
