OL,6,F"The public must have confidence that
OL,7,Fbarristers will act responsibly and
OL,8,Fuphold the law. The tribunal's
OL,9,Fdecision to suspend Mr Hickey until
OL,10,Fthe completion of the sentence imposed
OL,11,Fby the crown court demonstrates the
OL,12,Fimportance of maintaining public
OL,13,Fconfidence in the profession and that
OL,14,Fserious criminal convictions are
OL,15,Fincompatible with practice at the bar."
OL,17,FHamish Hickey has not responded to
OL,18,Frequests for comment.
