OL,6,FOn 9 January, the BSB disbarred a man
OL,7,Frecently called to the bar because a
OL,8,Funiversity had investigated him for
OL,9,Fcopying an essay.
OL,11,FOn 24 November, a barrister was
OL,12,Fdisbarred for producing five invoices
OL,13,Fto be paid into his own name, rather
OL,14,Fthan the chambers for which he worked,
OL,15,Fwhich "avoided financial obligations
OL,16,Fto his chambers".
OL,18,FNeither had committed a crime, but
OL,19,Fboth lost their jobs because they had
OL,20,Fbeen deemed guilty of "dishonesty".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G12/14
